President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Mississippi due to the effects of Hurricane Zeta. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of George, Greene, Hancock, Harrison, Jackson, and Stone are eligible for federal funding, which can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid individuals and business owners in their recovery. State, tribal, and eligible governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, can also receive federal funding for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Brett H. Howard has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by calling the provided toll-free numbers. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.